In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims October 9, 2016, as Leif Erikson Day in honor of the Scandinavian explorer who is believed to be the first European to reach North America. The proclamation recognizes the contributions of Nordic Americans and their influence on the country. It also highlights the strong ties and partnerships between the United States and Nordic countries. The article encourages Americans to observe the day with appropriate ceremonies, activities, and programs to honor Nordic-American heritage.